values.name: Dental Complete
values.tooltip: This is one of the nations largest dental preferred provider networks. Providers have agreed to accept certain fees (allowed amounts). Although the patient still may pay less out of pocket than seeing an out-of-network dentist, the discount is not as deep as with the Prime network.

values.name: Dental Prime
values.tooltip: This is the smaller network, but with deeper discounts. Providers have agreed to accept lower fees (allowed amounts) than the Complete network, resulting in less out-of-pocket expense to the patient.

categories.name: Product Design
categories.tooltip: Classic, Enhanced and Value products have no waiting periods. Voluntary plans have a 12 month waiting period applied to major, endo, perio, oral surgery and orthodontia services if applicable. Waiting periods are waived for all members enrolling during implementation if the group has prior comparable dental coverage.

values.name: Active
values.tooltip: Active PPO plans are plans that have a richer co-insurance in-network versus out-of network; e.g., 100%/80%/50% in network and 80%/60%/50% out of network.

values.name: Passive
values.tooltip: Passive PPO plans have the same co-insurance in and out of network; e.g., 100%/80%/50% in and out of network.

categories.name: Endo/Perio/Oral Surgery
categories.tooltip: Endodontic Services are most commonly known as Root Canals and similar services. Periodontal Services are most commonly known as Scaling and Root Planing, and treatment of Gum Disease. Oral Surgery is most commonly thought of as tooth extraction(i.e. removal of Wisdom Teeth). These services are covered by the same percentages as either the Basic Services or the Major Services. For information on how the Endo/Perio/Oral Services are covered on your selected plan, please refer to your Summary of Benefits.
